                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-146-off783 t18311201-146-crimeloc785"></join>, on the 1st of November, about half-past six o'clock in the evening; there was another man with him, who took the umbrella, and gave it to the prisoner - the other man then took another; they both went off - the prisoner was but two or three inches from the other man when he took them: I went into the shop, and told what I had seen - the prisoner went down Gray's Inn-lane, where he was taken with this umbrella.</p>
